  "text": "An analytical solution to the Navier-Stokes equations is available for the one-dimensional shock layer problem, [CITATION_1] and can be employed as a benchmark for numerical methods. Let subscripts 1 and 2 denote states upstream and downstream of the shock wave, respectively. As a test case we simulated a steady shock wave, with shock Mach number M s = 1.5. The upstream conditions are:",
